runs.comm: short and pulled firmly around the corner, that didn't get up as much as anticipated, but nicely controlled all the same
full length, hint of outswing, defended into the covers. Looking for the single but nothing on offer
back of a length, defended with busy footwork in front of middle
a fraction of width, met with a straight bat and pushed to point
angling down the leg side, no bat on an attempted glance but good calling from Mustard
banged in short, Mustard swings into a hook shot, but no contact
width outside off stump, slashed violently through the gully region, down to third man
Mustard makes room to leg, Martin spots him going and follows him well. A single is the upshot as the ball is pushed straight down the ground and picked up at mid-on
wide of the crease, angling back into the right-hander, who is beaten as he wafts outside off. That's a teasing line
into position early for a pushed drive, but cover fields well and Wright has to scramble for the crease, which he does well
a thick outside edge, Mustard totally squared up as he aimed over midwicket, and that's sailed all the way over third man! Remarkable
wild, down the leg side
good yorker, dug out well, and a scampered single to end the over
cracking delivery, inswinging yorker to the left-hander, who is knocked off his feet as he gets his toes out of the way
smacked down the ground! A filthy looking shot - that's something I'd play, head up, leaning backwards, no hope of middling it. But he did, and long-off had no chance
another filthy smear, no contact as he swings to leg
and yet more filthy slugging. There's no other word for it. But when he connects, all is forgiven
overpitched, and he pays the price, another scythe through the line, and hit straight down the ground
clubbed firmly to midwicket. The end of an intentful over ...
tucked off the hip - Mustard's most measured shot of the morning - and a simple single to short fine leg
wallop! Three steps down the ground, turns a good-length ball into a half-volley, and cover can't cut that off
more striding out of the crease, this one is met low on the bat, and mid-on sweeps round to field behind the stumps
another attempted yorker, a fraction misdirected, but effective enough
wide outside off stump, but angling in, Wright has a swish but can't make contact
clobbered through point with a full swing and even fuller followthrough! Too wide from Martin, and it cost him dear
Full length, into the slot, deposited over long-on. That was travelling
gives himself room, but shouldn't have bothered. Hitchcock holds it back and Mustard's wild swing isn't properly timed
The covers are taking a pummelling now, as Wright's confidence begins to soar. Down the track again, and that one whistles low but airborne into the gap
slower ball again, Wright climbs into it, perhaps gets a touch underneath it, but that clears the short boundary by eight metres!
drilled into the covers again. Trouble at 't'mill for New Zealand
pinged down the ground, and a lame attempt at an interception from mid-off. He gets half a hand on it, but that's not enough
mowed across the line and that scuds over cow corner for another maximum. This is getting brutal
banged in a touch shorter, and Wright's helicopter swish almost takes him off his feet. No contact though
repeat performance! This is the January sales, carried over into the first week of February
how did that go for four? Wright heaved across the line again, seemed not to have got more than a toothpick's worth of bat on it, but no-one came close to cutting it off at long-on

and that's the end of that! The adrenalin was pumping for Wright, and he couldn't resist swinging at the best delivery of the over. Almost yorker length, straight and angling in. Takes out middle stump to end an entertaining innings
off the mark straightaway. Not perfectly timed, but has the legs to roll right to the edge of the rope at deep cover
good length, outside off and angling in. Mustard defends with a tentative jab. Unusual reticence ...
thumped through the covers
slower ball, defended into the covers with a measured push
angled into the left-hander from round the wicket, a big baseball-style mow, under-edged through to the keeper who fields well
low full toss, raps Pietersen on the pad as he walks across the stumps and that is absolutely plumb!
shuffles across to clip his first ball to leg, and that's the end of a very tidy first over
good-length ball, nipping back in and defended into the covers
slightly shorter, and bounces a touch. Pushed into the covers

dabbed into the leg-side, Bell wanted the single but didn't exactly motor for it. Ross Taylor at mid-on hurtled round, picked up well, and pinged down the non-striker's stumps from about ten yards. Billy Bowden calls for the replay, but Bell has already given up the ghost
short, too short. And too slow as well. Mustard has all the time he needs to pick his spot, and that spot is somewhere over extra cover
into position for an exaggerated sweep from way outside off, but not timed
an urgent thump into the covers
round the wicket, and beaten. Well bowled

smeared high and handsome, scraping the long white cloud itself, and Mills at mid-on has to back-pedal to take a steepling chance. He does well, and that's the end of an aggressive and impressive innings from Mustard
outside off stump, just back of a length, clumped into the covers to get off the mark
clipped into the leg-side
pushed up to mid-off again. A sudden wave of calm sweeps over the shot selection
left alone outside off stump! Good grief, how improbable ...
nudged into the leg side again
a slow bouncer, well, a short ball at any rate. Shah completely mistimes a swing to leg
he doesn't miss out this time. Into position early, and put away well behind square
misses out with a clip to leg
clipped down to fine leg
bouncer, beaten
clipped to deep midwicket
thick outside edge squirts to third man
cut into the off side without any power
turned into the leg side. New Zealand will be delighted to keep this down to a run a ball
run down to third man with a very open face
firm push  to extra cover
a dab-sweep loops over square leg, never a catch despite yells to the contrary
steered to third man ... he likes that shot
pulled with a lot of bottom hand from outside off stump, up and over the square-leg boundary
slower long hop, pulled inches wide of a diving Kyle Mills at backward square leg ... great effort from the man on the rope
steps back and cuts to deep point. Styris going well outside the off stump after being thumped for 10 in two on the leg
driven to long-on
straight and full, clipped to midwicket
hammered high over long-on, Billy Bowden goes his slightly silly one-legged signalling
driven past extra cover and with the boundary so short it's four ... it wouldn't be on most grounds as he didn't exactly thump it
leg-stump full toss, clipped to Ryder at deep midwicket
a rare dot ball as the on drive hits the non striker and bounces to the bowler
driven to the man our in the deep on the off side
back of a length and Shah defends
pushed to extra cover for a strolled single
outside off and Collingwood pulls out of the shot as it gets a bit big on him
driven from wide of off stump to long-off
kiss of death there ... full and no more than placed through the covers, no power but all about where he aimed it
slower ball completely deceives Shah who is left swinging at air
steered to long-on
full, dug out and it bobbles to long-on
he follows Collingwood who moves to leg, he has to be content with a single into the leg side
Collingwood also moves to leg, again Ryder follows and the outcome is the same
wider outside off, driven to long-off
clip-swish to deep midwicket
an ugly heave and a thick inside edge goes to long leg
very wide and full, squeezed to third man
full toss but the shot is mistimed and  dribbles to long-off
firm drive beats a diving extra cover but long-off is wider to protect the short boundary
a big an early step to the off allows him to pull a full toss past a diving midwicket and there's no protection out there
pretty much the same, a shimmy to the off, a full toss, and this one goes to the left of midwicket and races away
hammered to the right of long-on and How makes a superb diving stop. it bounced kindly but he did really well
deft and wristy paddle goes for a one-bounce four to fine leg
super shot, driven off one knee over long-off .
driven into the ground and back to the bowler

Shah comes down the track, misses it and McCullum fumbles and misses a certain stumping ... he takes the bails off with his gloves and the crowd thinks he has been bowled ... as does Shah for a moment
driven high towards wide long-off, two fielders converge and it falls between them a yard from the rope as they hang back and bounces for four
full toss paddle-swept for a one-bounce four
long hop gets exactly what it deserved, smashed high over square leg
heaved to deep midwicket
wide and full, swinging wider and Shah has to really stretch to get anything on it, it dribbles into the off side for a scrambled single
a are off-side shot from Collingwood - it was so wide he had no choice - and well stopped by point as there was nobody behind him
full toss swung along the ground to deep midwicket
wide, Shah steps back and thumps that to deep cover
full toss swung to deep midwicket ... that's almost a stock shot in Twenty20
full but very wide
well caught by Fulton at deep midwicket but he can't stay inside the rope
and it's a one-ball reprieve as Shah smacks the ball to Taylor at long-off ... he was right back on the boundary and had to check where his feet where after he had caught it
and he obliges ... short, he shapes to hit over long-on but seriously underclubs and the catch is taken ten yards inside the boundary
short, Mascarenhas steps back and uppercut-slap-slashes the ball into the crowd beyond backward point
steps to off, he responds by banging the ball in ridiculously short, a wide is called, McCullum throws down the stumps. All the fun of the fair ...
pushed firmly to third man, enough time to scurry back for the second
Swann steps to leg, Mills follows and fires one in at his feet which he does well to steer to backward point
good delivery, in at the crease but Mascarenhas changes his intended shot and guides the ball to the third-man boundary
he steps to leg and Mills fires it down the off side ... close to a wide

pushed from wide of the off stump to deep cover, Mascarenhas takes on Ryder's arm and loses by a foot. A really good throw as he was off balance and McCullum only had to gather and whip the bails off ..
Broad leans back and swats the ball high ... Ryder under it 15 yards inside the midwicket boundary hold the steepler
